	                <h1>
    	                <span id="Template_NewsDate1_lblDate" style="float:right">12 June 2012 13:51</span>

	                    Summer drink and drug driving campaign, mid-way results


	                    <span id="Template_ctl08_lblMessage"><font color="Red"></font></span>

	                </h1>
                	
<p class="MsoNormal"></p>
<table summary="box" class="ImmControlAlign_Right">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img width="250" alt="ACPOS Drink Drive" title="ACPOS Drink Drive" src="/images/acpos_dd.jpg" height="244"/></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p class="legend">Half-way results show that&nbsp;motorists are</p>
<p class="legend">still&nbsp;ignoring&nbsp;warnings&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Motorists who persist in driving after taking alcohol or drugs
face being on the losing side this summer &ndash; losing their licence
and perhaps their vehicle and livelihood too.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">At the half-way stage in the ACPOS Summer
Drink and Drug Driving Campaign, results show that people are still
ignoring warnings and continuing to choose to drive whilst under
the influence of drink or drugs.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Figures for the first week of the campaign
(June 4 &ndash;11) show that across Scotland, 111 people have been
reported for drink driving and in addition three people were
detected driving whilst being unfit through alcohol with five unfit
through drugs.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">A total of 15 vehicles have been seized for
consideration of forfeiture by the court.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In one incident in Aberdeen, a female driver
crashed into two parked cars and was found to be more than four
times over the legal limit. She was also charged with dangerous
driving.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In another incident in West Lothian, a woman
was found to be driving whilst nearly three times the legal limit.
Her 15 year old son was a passenger in the car.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Chief Superintendent Derek Robertson of
Lothian and Borders Police is the Road Casualty Reduction Lead for
the Association of Chief Police Officers in Scotland. He said: &ldquo;The
figures are marginally down on this time last year and that is
refreshing to note.&nbsp; We welcome that trend and it is good to
see that the number of people caught for driving whilst unfit
through drugs has decreased by 60%. Hopefully the message is
getting across.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&ldquo;However it remains concerning that 111
drivers across Scotland have still opted to get behind the wheel
when they are clearly incapable of driving safely. They pose a
danger to other innocent road users and that is unacceptable.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&ldquo;There are increased patrols on Scotland&rsquo;s
roads at present and the police are focused on catching drivers who
take to the road whilst unfit through drink or drugs.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;Officers will continue with this initiative until June 18 and I
would encourage the public who suspect anyone of driving whilst
under the influence of drink or drugs to contact the Police or
Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111.&rdquo;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Regional breakdown and incidents of
note.</strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Central Scotland</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Central Scotland Police force area, six
people were caught driving under the influence of alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Dumfries and Galloway</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Dumfries and Galloway Constabulary
force area, three people were caught driving under the influence of
alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">About 1810 hours on 9 June a motor car was
stopped in Lockerbie after officers noticed the vehicle being
driven with the rear nearside door wide open.&nbsp; A drunk female
was found in the rear of the vehicle and the 50 year old male
driver subsequently provided a breath sample nearly three time the
legal limit. He was also charged with driving without a licence and
no insurance&nbsp; and application has been made for forfeiture of
the vehicle.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Fife</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Fife Constabulary force area, seven
people were caught driving under the influence of alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">A male driver provided a breath sample of over
three times the legal limit, this is the second time he has been
caught in 2 weeks &ndash; request for vehicle forfeiture (moped).&nbsp;
This incident was as a result of anonymous tip-off from a member of
the public.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">One incident involved a 26 years old man who
subsequently provided a breath sample nearly three times the legal
limit. He had failed to stop after an accident and thereafter the
vehicle was set on fire outside a number of dwellings, potentially
putting the occupants at risk.&nbsp; Fife Fire and Rescue attended
promptly and dealt with the fire ensuring safety of public.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Grampian</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Grampian Police force area, 12 people
were caught driving under the influence of alcohol and a further
two were found driving whilst unfit through drugs.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">On 8 June at 2.30am, a 29 year old woman
driver was stopped in Aberdeen, she was charged with driving whilst
unfit through drugs.&nbsp; She was also charged with having no road
tax or motor insurance, being in possession of drugs and
shoplifting.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">On 10 June at 4.45pm, a 45 year old woman
crashed her vehicle into two parked cars in Aberdeen.&nbsp; She
provided a breath sample of more than FOUR times the legal limit
and was also charged with dangerous driving. (No vehicle forfeiture
request was made as her vehicle was extensively damaged in the
crash).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Lothian and Borders</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Lothian and Borders Police force area,
eight people were caught driving under the influence of
alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Following an anonymous phone call a 36yr old
male was stopped in Uphall, West Lothian at 2.30pm. He provided a
breath sample of more that three times the legal limit. He was also
charged with being in possession of air rifle in public place.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Following a collision on the A 801 at
Westfield, West Lothian, a 47 year old woman provided a breath
sample of nearly three times the legal limit. &nbsp;Her 15 yr old
son was a passenger at the time of the offence and a charge under
S12 of the CYPS Act was also libelled.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Northern</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Northern Constabulary force area, 11
people were caught driving under the influence of alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">A 38 yr old man is due to appear at Inverness
Sheriff Court in connection with alleged drink driving and speeding
offences.&nbsp; His car was stopped on the A9 after being detected
travelling at speeds in excess of 120mph.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Strathclyde</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Strathclyde Police force area, 44
people were caught driving under the influence of alcohol, a
further three were detected driving whilst unfit through alcohol
and three were found driving whilst unfit through drugs.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Tayside</h3>
<p class="MsoNormal">In the Tayside Police force area, 10 people
were caught driving under the influence of alcohol.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">About 8.30pm on 5 June acting on information
from the public, officers stopped and apprehended the driver of a
vehicle for drunk driving in Kinross. The 40 year old woman
subsequently provided a breath sample twice the legal limit and was
also charged with carrying a 14 year old child in the vehicle to
their danger.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">About 3.10am on 10 June officers stopped a 40
year old man regarding his manner of driving in Arbroath.&nbsp;
Alcohol was sensed but the driver refused the initial breath test
and also the station procedure. He was detained in custody and
forfeiture of his vehicle applied for.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">About 5.45am on 10 June in Westway, Arbroath
acting on information from the public, officers stopped a 34 year
old male who subsequently provided a breath sample over three time
the legal limit. He was detained in custody and forfeiture of his
vehicle applied for.</p>
